<title>FRANCE: French budget deficit 241.3 bln Ffr end-May-fin min.</title>
<headline>French budget deficit 241.3 bln Ffr end-May-fin min.</headline>
<dateline>PARIS 1997-07-16</dateline>
<text>
<p>The French budget deficit at the end of May stood at 241.3 billion francs, the finance ministry said on Friday.</p>
<p>The figure compared with a deficit of 253.5 billion francs</p>
<p>at the end of May 1996, it said in a statement.</p>
<p>The ministry gave the following breakdown of budget</p>
<p>receipts: (figures in billions, year on year changes in percent,</p>
<p>1997 year forecast):</p>
<p> REVENUES			end May 97  May 96  pct	 1997</p>
<p> Net tax receipts		 577.4    569.0   1.5    1,395.3</p>
<p>  of which: -- income tax     150.2    153.5  -2.1	291.8</p>
<p>  -- net company tax	     46.4     45.2   2.7	144.8</p>
<p>  -- petrol duties		 57.6     57.5   0.2	151.9</p>
<p>  -- net Value Added Tax	261.2    255.0   2.4	635.2</p>
<p>  -- miscellaneous		 62.0     57.8   7.3	171.6</p>
<p> Non-tax receipts		  42.0     37.4  12.3	155.1</p>
<p> Local authority, EU charges -108.4   -104.0   4.2     -253.9</p>
<p> General budget receipts	535.9    529.4   1.2    1,296.5</p>
<p>SPENDING			end May 97  May 96  pct</p>
<p> Ordinary civil spending	583.6    572.4   2.0</p>
<p> of which debt		    117.5    118.3  -0.7</p>
<p> Capital civil spending	  31.9     40.1 -20.4</p>
<p> Ordinary military spending    49.9     48.4   3.1</p>
<p> Capital military spending     33.1     38.3 -13.6</p>
<p> TOTAL BUDGET SPENDING	  698.5    699.2  -0.1</p>
<p>BALANCE</p>
<p> Total net spending	     698.5    699.2    NA</p>
<p> Total net receipts	     535.9    529.4   1.2</p>
<p> General budget deficit	-162.6   -169.8</p>
<p> Special Treasury Accounts    -78.7    -83.7</p>
<p> TOTAL CENTRAL GOVT DEFICIT  -241.3   -253.5</p>
